# Production hosting — MCP-first

When the task touches **production auth**, **email**, **DNS**, **env vars**, **deploys**, or **go-live** for brisbaneservers.com:

1. **Do it yourself** via MCP or documented APIs before asking the user to click dashboards.
2. **Read first:** `docs/operations/HOSTING_MCP_WORKSPACE.md`, `docs/operations/PRODUCTION_GO_LIVE_STATUS.md`, `docs/operations/FEATURES_NOT_BUILT.md`.

**Production API is Cloudflare Worker only** — not Render. Render is legacy/decommission: `docs/operations/RENDER_MCP.md`.

## MCP servers (`.cursor/mcp.json`)

| Server | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| `cloudflare-api` | Pages env, DNS, Workers, Email Routing (`execute` tool) |
| `render` | **Legacy only** — decommission, historical logs (optional) |

Canonical API: `https://api.brisbaneservers.com/api`

## Auth email (Resend)

- **Do not** leave `AUTH_EMAIL_FROM` on `onboarding@resend.dev` in production (403 for non-test recipients).
- Verified sending domains in DNS: **`mail.brisbaneservers.com`** and **`brisbaneservers.com`** (Resend DKIM/SPF in Cloudflare).
- Production `AUTH_EMAIL_FROM` (worker secret): `Brisbane Servers <support@brisbaneservers.com>` when root domain verified; interim `support@mail.brisbaneservers.com` if needed.
- After changing **worker** secrets, redeploy edge worker and test send.

## Google OAuth

- Check `GET /api/auth/oauth/status` on the live API (`api.brisbaneservers.com`).
- Client ID (production): `1040878189962-o0que80vsplu0vghos3ogdgjdakpvdda.apps.googleusercontent.com`
- Redirect URI (Worker): `https://api.brisbaneservers.com/api/auth/oauth/google/callback` (must match Google Console **Authorized redirect URIs**).
- Set secrets via `.\website-brisbaneservers.com\scripts\configure-google-oauth.ps1` (worker secrets + user env).

## After infra changes

- Run `npm run verify:production -- --api https://api.brisbaneservers.com` from `website-brisbaneservers.com`.
- Update `docs/operations/PRODUCTION_GO_LIVE_STATUS.md` with date and what changed.
- Never print secrets (`CRON_SECRET`, API keys, generated passwords) in chat.
